Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.33,0:00:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got more humility than anybody in the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.10,0:00:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where you sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.46,0:00:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get here, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.93,0:00:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the chair there?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.42,0:00:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.28,0:00:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.53,0:00:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness, this is exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.34,0:00:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows what could happen next?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.79,0:00:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful, that's a little cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.61,0:00:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what's happening next?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.71,0:00:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.35,0:00:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.14,0:00:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,She's my living, breathing teleprompter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.60,0:01:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The one and only Super Susie.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.85,0:01:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Super Susie.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.81,0:01:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of Susies, but not a Super Susie.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.62,0:01:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens next, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.93,0:01:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess we'll kind of wait for people to kind of follow,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.18,0:01:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,come back in, and then we'll start.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.56,0:01:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have more slides to do or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.17,0:01:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're about one minute early.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.84,0:01:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So what would you like to talk about while we're waiting for people to get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.18,0:01:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have more slides to do or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.79,0:01:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.60,0:01:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we have more slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.75,0:01:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So what would you like to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.20,0:01:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to talk about whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.26,0:01:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,People are interested in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.21,0:01:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How to get rich and famous and even with your enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.56,0:01:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.26,0:01:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.01,0:01:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.56,0:01:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I better use this or they're going to get mad at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.84,0:01:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.95,0:01:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see if I can get it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.21,0:02:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the battery standing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.40,0:02:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.41,0:02:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.31,0:02:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Dermot?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.18,0:02:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.93,0:02:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,New battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.28,0:02:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Dermot?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.72,0:02:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As we know from previous lectures,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.34,0:02:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't the wealth and the fame of being famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.55,0:02:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the glamour of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.93,0:02:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The glamour is a specific energy that we project onto things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.43,0:02:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not intrinsic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.55,0:02:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's projected onto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.90,0:02:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.90,0:02:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.38,0:02:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So glamour.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.77,0:02:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamour, is that, would you classify ego as, the ego as glamour?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.99,0:02:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Only in a sideways kind of a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.46,0:02:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.50,0:02:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.03,0:02:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I think it, it's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.18,0:02:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're sort of glamourizing your own thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.12,0:03:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what I believe or what I think is what's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.55,0:03:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a certain egocentricity to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.13,0:03:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The world, the universe doesn't care what you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.13,0:03:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.56,0:03:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.62,0:03:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.58,0:03:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe doesn't care what you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.36,0:03:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It don't give a ribbity damn, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.18,0:03:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.62,0:03:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, what about, we always talk about the,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.62,0:03:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of entrapment there is for, say, a high spiritual being, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.34,0:03:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that you would refer to as, quote, a guru.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.00,0:03:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You, we, we talk quite often about what the three entrapments are of, of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.13,0:03:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, such as sex, money, um, fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.75,0:03:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Fame, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.13,0:03:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sex, money, and fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.53,0:03:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the three entrapments that you say in golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.34,0:03:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, because gurus fall right and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.68,0:03:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And, and they also fall for peculiar things, like sex with little boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.41,0:03:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.87,0:04:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Which sounds so bizarre that it's unimaginable, but it is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.27,0:04:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.61,0:04:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was just wondering, you know, can you kind of, um, when, is it, they don't really start out that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.83,0:04:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It just seems that they develop these tendencies later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.68,0:04:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They seem to, and, uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.56,0:04:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So they start out at a high, and then they're kind of like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.81,0:04:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.82,0:04:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To the, to the most surprising people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.75,0:04:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, then later on you feel they've fallen into the trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.10,0:04:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I say, I can't imagine who would find all that attractive, but some kind of, uh, malevolent negative energy comes around.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.60,0:04:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.48,0:04:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So because you, if you're standing for truth, then you're the, uh, the enemy of falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.02,0:04:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And evil sort of ferrets around trying to find a crack in your armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.49,0:04:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, it, it's, uh, actual literal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.72,0:05:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Literally, from the demonic realms, demons literally look for cracks in your armor that they can get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hold the arm on that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.68,0:05:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's actually a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.23,0:05:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only that, but I saw, I saw the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.99,0:05:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You could actually see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.66,0:05:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember somebody who was supposedly a pretty high spiritual teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.31,0:05:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.47,0:05:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you just give it away to the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.43,0:05:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what you've learned, give it away, read a book, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.31,0:05:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, the demons flew out of his head and they were furious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.93,0:05:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually saw them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.23,0:05:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm not clairvoyant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.41,0:05:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I don't see any of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.18,0:05:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Buddha had demons that tried to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.17,0:05:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.99,0:05:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.58,0:05:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said that when he, uh, that the demons came.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.88,0:05:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember being attacked by demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.70,0:05:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, it's, it's literally.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.79,0:06:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A fact that demons look for any crack in your armor that they can get in vanity or, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.18,0:06:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,sexual proclivities or wealth or fame, all the traditional, um, traps that the guru is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.85,0:06:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so-called gurus fall into.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.93,0:06:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when I wrote the last book or two, uh, uh, I wasn't allowed to even use the word
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.37,0:06:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,guru.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.45,0:06:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that I used the arm and said, do not even use the word because the word itself is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.98,0:06:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,false.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.98,0:06:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, defamation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.13,0:06:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.13,0:06:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.13,0:06:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, I thought that was very interesting that we needed to share that, um, with people
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.41,0:06:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because, um, you know, just because you followed someone and they're first starting out, does
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.18,0:06:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it, you know, they can change and it can't be false.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.06,0:06:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.06,0:06:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't think they would, but, uh, there, if there's a crack in the armor, the demons
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.82,0:06:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.86,0:06:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.62,0:06:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.62,0:06:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have friends that were really taken to the cleaners financially.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:06:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.18,0:07:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,By big names.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.18,0:07:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.56,0:07:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more money, more and more money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.20,0:07:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.20,0:07:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And every time they turn around, there's more money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.20,0:07:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.20,0:07:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what in the hell you'd do with all that money if you had it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.20,0:07:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it would be a plague.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.20,0:07:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have to put it in the closets or under the bed or, I don't know what they would do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.20,0:07:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.20,0:07:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what good it would do you, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.20,0:07:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think people associate money with power.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.20,0:07:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.20,0:07:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.47,0:07:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.47,0:07:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.47,0:07:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.47,0:07:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.47,0:07:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.47,0:07:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.47,0:07:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.47,0:07:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.56,0:07:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.07,0:07:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.07,0:07:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.07,0:07:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.07,0:07:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.30,0:07:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.30,0:07:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.49,0:07:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.49,0:07:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That gives them power.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.49,0:07:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.49,0:07:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.49,0:07:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's, kind of, like an ego power trip too because the more money they have, the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.50,0:07:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,bigger the place they can do, the bigger, you know, following, so they attribute that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.12,0:07:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to, I think that type of feeling is what comes up maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.48,0:07:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the people, I knew a lot of people back east that came from, you know, long time wealthy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.76,0:07:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,families, and they were just a very simple, plain people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.81,0:08:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They never put on the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.62,0:08:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.08,0:08:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.12,0:08:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for anybody and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.47,0:08:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,just simplicity of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.76,0:08:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,life because
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.61,0:08:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,once you've already bought a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.04,0:08:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,expensive cars and cruised around
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.01,0:08:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in them and you lived in a fancy address
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.10,0:08:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean I lived on 5th Avenue
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.13,0:08:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking at a 5th Avenue
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.87,0:08:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,socialite. I lived at
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.49,0:08:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,958 5th Avenue
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.67,0:08:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.05,0:08:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.50,0:08:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.06,0:08:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so it doesn't do you too much good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.08,0:08:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You say well that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.96,0:08:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.34,0:08:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That 10 bucks
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.62,0:08:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,will get you in the door of the theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.29,0:08:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.98,0:08:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we all ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.15,0:08:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. We were just chatting right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.91,0:08:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah we're just chatting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.94,0:08:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted everyone to be back from lunch before we really started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.87,0:08:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. We're back from the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.53,0:08:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.70,0:08:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.84,0:09:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What comes up next now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.01,0:09:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got more slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.01,0:09:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh we have more slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.38,0:09:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Slippy slidey. Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.23,0:09:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Slippy slidey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.22,0:09:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okie doke. Take that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.08,0:09:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissist. Rich and famous is narcissistic and be pleased with the direction you're going and your alignment instead of just where you are on the on the trail.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.05,0:10:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If your life is dedicated to truth and purity and goodness and being benign and uplifting towards all of life you're already there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.39,0:10:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point in seeking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.36,0:10:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no end to a spiritual alignment because it's a way of a way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.96,0:10:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.86,0:10:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't have any beginning point and it doesn't have any end point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.25,0:10:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think it has a lot of a karmic propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.98,0:10:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of karmic propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.17,0:10:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.84,0:10:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a high percentage of spiritual evolution and commitment is primarily spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.25,0:10:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, they're car makers, this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.42,0:10:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.73,0:10:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you got bad karma?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.47,0:10:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez, it was bottom of the barrel for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.01,0:10:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you climbed up from the bottom of the barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.72,0:10:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way you get good karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.11,0:10:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You could get even with somebody, and instead you forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.03,0:10:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You forgive people because they don't know any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.01,0:10:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't realize any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.33,0:11:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't evolved to a higher level.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.45,0:11:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a way, people can't help being who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.29,0:11:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A nasty burglar is a nasty burglar,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.32,0:11:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's about as good as he can get right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.58,0:11:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He could learn to be a nice burglar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.65,0:11:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A pleasant burglar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.24,0:11:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Straighten up the house after you mess it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.50,0:11:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we know somebody who interviews criminals and burglars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.67,0:11:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and people like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.97,0:11:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it's a very interesting adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.47,0:11:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, so be pleased with the direction that your life is going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.94,0:11:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, don't be concerned about being enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.11,0:11:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be as loving and forgiving towards all of life as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.40,0:11:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Cherish all of life and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.25,0:12:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Cherish all of life and all its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.01,0:12:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So you walk over the beetle instead of stepping on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.62,0:12:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, because it has life,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.99,0:12:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and you cherish the life in that little beetle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.04,0:12:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.84,0:12:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So you give up the glamour of success,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.20,0:12:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially if you are successful,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.52,0:12:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean if you're successful and live in certain areas and you're a multi-millionaire,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.89,0:12:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so is everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So what else is new?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.75,0:12:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Choose to make a decision instead of just hope, hoping to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.75,0:12:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Choose and make that decision now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.98,0:12:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That I've made a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.21,0:12:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to live my life to the highest level that it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.21,0:12:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to live my life to the highest level that it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to live my life to the highest level that it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.97,0:12:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And fulfill my potential, uh, via divine grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.97,0:12:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And fulfill my potential, uh, via divine grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.97,0:12:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we ask God's help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.00,0:12:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We ask God's help to lead us in the direction through divine grace to our ultimate goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.15,0:13:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We ask God's help to lead us in the direction through divine grace to our ultimate goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.15,0:13:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, what's next? Anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.58,0:13:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You learn to become flexible instead of rigid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.79,0:13:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't, if you can't go this way, you go that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.86,0:13:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're, there's an easy malleability.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.87,0:13:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Cancel and then I'll be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.36,0:13:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, happiness is nothing that you can set as a goal in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.51,0:13:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not happy now, you're not gonna be happy later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.51,0:13:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not happy now, then you set up goals for yourself that are not achievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.19,0:13:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.04,0:13:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm rich, then I'll be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.04,0:13:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of clutching and grasping.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.42,0:13:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, trying to seize things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.42,0:13:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So this has to do with grace, with gracefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.42,0:13:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So this has to do with grace, with gracefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.42,0:13:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So this has to do with grace, with gracefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.49,0:13:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the person, as they spiritually evolve,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.49,0:13:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes gracious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.49,0:13:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Gracious and graceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.49,0:13:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And gracious towards all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.58,0:14:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.58,0:14:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you're walking down, you see all those little bugs,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.58,0:14:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you walk around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.58,0:14:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't wanna walk too close to the bug
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.58,0:14:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because you'll scare them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.22,0:14:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I don't wanna scare the bug,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.22,0:14:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so I walk all the way around
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.63,0:14:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,then the little bug is happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.63,0:14:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If the little bug is happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.63,0:14:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,little bug is happy, then I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.09,0:14:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if we get flies
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.97,0:14:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in the house, what you do is you open the top
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.04,0:14:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the window and lower the screen
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.76,0:14:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,until the flies fly out
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.00,0:14:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you close it up again
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.26,0:14:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,now that the flies are free and happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.29,0:14:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.20,0:14:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,clutching and grasping.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.10,0:14:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarify your goals and your ideals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.82,0:14:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that all
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.63,0:14:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,value is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.38,0:14:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All value is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.54,0:14:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,arbitrary. What value
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.27,0:14:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you add to a thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.82,0:14:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,an arbitrary
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.02,0:15:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,selection. Whether you're rich
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.23,0:15:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and famous or whether you're poor and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.07,0:15:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,humble, in the end it's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.27,0:15:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,all the same because all
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.55,0:15:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,value is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.51,0:15:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All you can buy in the meantime is comfort
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.63,0:15:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and style.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.71,0:15:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Comfort and style.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.15,0:15:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is a map on a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.91,0:15:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,train of a plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.03,0:15:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.60,0:15:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A train.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.74,0:15:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.69,0:15:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Being happy means that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you take a nap when you're on a train
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.84,0:15:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or a plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.13,0:15:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember being
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.63,0:15:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,grounded for six hours in Greece
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.63,0:15:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,one time. They were having air
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.79,0:15:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,maneuvers of the military
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.05,0:16:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so we got grounded for six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.17,0:16:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Six hours on the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.22,0:16:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,ground was very boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.53,0:16:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, happily, after half an hour
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.20,0:16:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.79,0:16:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Six hours sitting there
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.44,0:16:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,frantically
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.39,0:16:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to push time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.29,0:16:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, a nap on a plane
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.75,0:16:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or a train. Live one
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.32,0:16:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,day at a time. That is certainly part
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.37,0:16:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 12-step program.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.72,0:16:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday is over and tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.27,0:16:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,never comes. You realize
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.57,0:16:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that tomorrow never comes because
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.42,0:16:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow it'll be, the next day
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.52,0:16:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,will be tomorrow. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.99,0:16:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,live one day
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.71,0:16:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time. Happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.13,0:16:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the small things of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.91,0:16:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of a kitty's purr
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.63,0:16:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or a dog's wagging
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.53,0:16:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,tail. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.89,0:16:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,what could be happier than
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.87,0:16:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,hearing a purr kitty? So, our kitties in the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.94,0:16:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,morning, I've got three of them on the bed, they're going
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.98,0:16:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,purr, purr, purr, purr,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.36,0:16:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,purr, purr. Three of them are
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.00,0:17:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,doing that at the same time. Purr, purr,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.20,0:17:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,purr, purr, purr, purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.87,0:17:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the dog comes around and puts her nose
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.09,0:17:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,over the top of the bed to make
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.07,0:17:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,sure that all three kitties are where they're supposed
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.09,0:17:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.67,0:17:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Her dog, she's a herding
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.26,0:17:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,dog, so her job is to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.17,0:17:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,all kitties are where they're
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.97,0:17:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.15,0:17:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, just living
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.28,0:17:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with animal life, I think, is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.95,0:17:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,very beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.08,0:17:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, I used to have patients who lived alone
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.34,0:17:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and were depressed, and I
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.13,0:17:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,told them, unless you get a dog, I can't treat you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.30,0:17:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because otherwise you're just egocentrically
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.78,0:17:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,concerned about
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.17,0:17:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself all the time, me, me, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And having
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.23,0:17:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a pet of any kind, or a canary, or a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.26,0:17:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,bird, or a kitty, or a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.40,0:17:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doggie, you start thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.24,0:17:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,something other than yourself is the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.27,0:17:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,doggie comfortable, did the doggie have
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.27,0:17:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,his dinner, did the doggie go out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you're thinking about another living thing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.44,0:17:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's happiness and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.24,0:17:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it's success.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.55,0:18:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, happiness is a kitty's purr
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.74,0:18:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or a dog's wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.54,0:18:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to have a monkey, and the monkey
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.54,0:18:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had a kinkajou.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.15,0:18:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A kinkajou is a South American
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.71,0:18:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,honey bear, and I had it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.67,0:18:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in a cage hanging over a bathtub
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.34,0:18:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in some place I lived, and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.73,0:18:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the kinkajou's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.73,0:18:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,fur got dull,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.39,0:18:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and his eyes got dull, and he lost
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.49,0:18:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,his appetite. So
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.99,0:18:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,intuition hit me, so I went
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.99,0:18:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,out and I bought a monkey,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.06,0:18:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I hung the monkey in a cage over the bathtub
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.30,0:18:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in another hook, so here is the kinkajou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.25,0:18:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,here, and the monkey there, and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.19,0:18:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they hated each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.43,0:18:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The kinkajou hated the monkey,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.43,0:18:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and the monkey would throw things at the kinkajou.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.16,0:18:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But the kinkajou's fur
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.35,0:18:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,got shiny and glossy, and his eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.20,0:18:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,sparkled, and he was quite happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.75,0:18:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So my intuition
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.45,0:18:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,was right, and so the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.30,0:18:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.41,0:18:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be related to other
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.52,0:19:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,living things, and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.04,0:19:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to love the woods as you go
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.47,0:19:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,through the woods, to love your garden as
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.52,0:19:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you love. So, faith
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.49,0:19:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,versus skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.99,0:19:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratitude for what you have
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.80,0:19:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.30,0:19:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.13,0:19:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be detached than to crave
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.00,0:19:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,things. Some people think
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.78,0:19:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,if you want a thing, it's because you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.86,0:19:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,crave it long enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.41,0:19:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, the thing is to become
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.99,0:19:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,light-hearted about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.01,0:19:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and detached.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.96,0:19:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you win the lottery, you win it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.92,0:19:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't, you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.57,0:19:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you get hung up and craving to win
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.88,0:19:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the lottery, even if you win it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.07,0:19:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,your life's going to be horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.47,0:19:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's stories on television,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.26,0:19:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the lives of people who have won the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.80,0:19:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of them was a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.45,0:19:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the divorce rate was 100%,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.54,0:19:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,suicide rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.59,0:19:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are the people who became
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.31,0:19:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,instant millionaires
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.27,0:19:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to see whether the world's glass
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.93,0:20:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is half full or it's half empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.50,0:20:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's optimism
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.57,0:20:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,versus pessimism.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.88,0:20:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're not too far along in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.50,0:20:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,be grateful and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.03,0:20:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,thank God I've got plenty of room
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.98,0:20:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to grow and gain and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,lots of pleasure to look forward to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.44,0:20:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're already rich and famous
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.00,0:20:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and happy, you haven't got too much left,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.64,0:20:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.81,0:20:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you can get a bad cold
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.33,0:20:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and wish it would go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.15,0:20:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Optimist versus pessimist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.48,0:20:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And to have
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.09,0:20:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual rather than material
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.42,0:20:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,gains.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.98,0:20:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the material gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.51,0:20:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.00,0:20:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,significance
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.00,0:20:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that God has seen to it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.01,0:20:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are well provided for
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.74,0:20:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.17,0:20:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,by good karma and grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.93,0:20:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm grateful
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.73,0:20:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have what we need
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.60,0:20:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to live life in a satisfactory manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.99,0:20:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.78,0:20:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.65,0:20:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Live one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.65,0:21:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This is again out of the 12-step program.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.25,0:21:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.57,0:21:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Detach versus craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.22,0:21:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Glass half full.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.40,0:21:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual versus material goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.18,0:21:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what's the next slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.46,0:21:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there another one?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.00,0:21:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there another slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.90,0:21:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there another slide waiting for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.44,0:21:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy, oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.38,0:21:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Good for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.78,0:21:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Good for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.82,0:21:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We made it through all the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.69,0:21:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my main ambition
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.02,0:21:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when I got up this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.08,0:21:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear God, please help us get through all the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.86,0:21:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.92,0:21:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.85,0:21:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not done?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.94,0:22:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be God's will that we have another
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.81,0:22:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,slide to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.07,0:22:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender to God's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.35,0:22:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Capacity to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.40,0:22:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.16,0:22:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrendering to God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.46,0:22:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is successfully letting go of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.80,0:22:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting go of thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.84,0:22:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have to do a certain thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.58,0:22:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that you must do a certain thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.69,0:22:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing to it that however it goes is going to be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.55,0:22:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.81,0:22:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So learning how to let go, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.07,0:22:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody knows how to grasp and grab.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.14,0:22:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody knows that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.22,0:22:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Even an idiot knows how to grasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.77,0:22:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But to know when to let go is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.50,0:22:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We're doing a book on letting go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.25,0:22:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's the name of the book, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.73,0:22:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.06,0:22:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.03,0:22:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Because then you drop the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.33,0:22:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You let go of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.40,0:23:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I let go of the book, and it's on the floor now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.74,0:23:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because society drives us in the other direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.82,0:23:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we learn the spiritual technique of letting a thing go,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.28,0:23:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,surrendering it, and open your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.50,0:23:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to be pleased with our progress,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.76,0:23:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,wherever we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.60,0:23:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to become a Buddha now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.39,0:23:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't have to become a Buddha now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.21,0:23:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You may never become a Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.03,0:23:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And Buddha, last time I spoke to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.83,0:23:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,says, I don't really need any help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.03,0:23:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you're detached from the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.61,0:23:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't really need much help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.93,0:23:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.95,0:23:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to avoid self-judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.15,0:23:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.34,0:23:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I being good?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.34,0:23:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I being bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.23,0:23:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.19,0:24:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean becoming unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.13,0:24:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.28,0:24:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So become self-aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.80,0:24:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than self-judgmental.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.98,0:24:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that the terms good and bad are all circumstantial.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.61,0:24:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Good as compared to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.05,0:24:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad as compared to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.78,0:24:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.19,0:24:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that in life, winning is provisional.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.15,0:24:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning is only temporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.99,0:24:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning is how you ever define it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.31,0:24:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning is not desiring fame or money.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.75,0:24:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.40,0:24:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you can be pissed for and win.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.19,0:24:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Take vows of poverty.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.48,0:24:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The less money you have, the better you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.57,0:24:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning is provisional.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.82,0:25:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's however you define it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.56,0:25:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And the shortest avenue is through simplicity
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.99,0:25:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.04,0:25:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.38,0:25:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.19,0:25:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Realistic expectations of yourself and the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.82,0:25:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.47,0:25:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,realistic expectations of what is common in human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.75,0:25:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We would like our governing body to be better than it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.13,0:25:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We would like our politicians to be better.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.43,0:25:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody and his brother should be doing a better job.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.17,0:25:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was possible, it would be so.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.91,0:25:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Value is in the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.23,0:25:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So whatever you think is valuable out there is a projection.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.04,0:25:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's similar to the whole concept about growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.50,0:25:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamour.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.41,0:25:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The value is, you know, glamour is in the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.74,0:25:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think it's wonderful and valuable, it'd be great.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.03,0:26:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,My father had a great big heavy gold ring with a great big amethyst in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.45,0:26:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He just loved that ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.25,0:26:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was a piano player.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.58,0:26:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So he'd play the piano and there would be this big gold ring with this big amethyst.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.80,0:26:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He just loved the amethyst stone, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.63,0:26:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And he wanted to leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.41,0:26:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, Dad, I'm never going to wear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.00,0:26:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A big gold ring that weighs a quarter of a pound, for God's sake, with a big amethyst.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.41,0:26:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I hate to decline it, but I'm never going to wear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.53,0:26:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the value is in the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.00,0:26:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like, give up skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.16,0:26:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.70,0:26:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.25,0:26:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to beat anybody who has a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.20,0:26:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because no matter what you do, it appears comical.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.50,0:26:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because how you hold it in mind is what creates the sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.59,0:27:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Accepting karmic propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.85,0:27:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, if things are not going your way, you say, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.68,0:27:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it could well be a reason for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.09,0:27:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,People who do past life regression often find what the karmic propensity was.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.16,0:27:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And it makes it extremely acceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.43,0:27:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.50,0:27:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened in what lifetime and what you did about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.25,0:27:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And one time I was having surgery, a lot of anesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.28,0:27:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the middle of it, I went back to that lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.60,0:27:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, good God, what did I ever do?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.50,0:27:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And suddenly, like, relived it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.02,0:27:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually, like, relived what had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.39,0:27:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think I've told that story before.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.75,0:27:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was a warrior, and I profoundly wounded my enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.16,0:27:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead of killing him, I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.35,0:27:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I left him there to die of his wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.77,0:27:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this lifetime, I then had to go through inguinal surgery without anesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.45,0:28:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And during that surgery, I thought, karmically, I must have done something to warrant this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.25,0:28:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.06,0:28:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not give him the coup de grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.36,0:28:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I left him to die of his wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.32,0:28:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the code of the warrior is to finish off your opponent if he's unable to finish himself off.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.77,0:28:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't have the moral courage to do that, or I wasn't trained enough to realize that was my responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.85,0:28:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When he's laying there crippled and horribly wounded, you say to the guy, you want to leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.72,0:28:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And the guy says, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.53,0:28:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You let him leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.18,0:28:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If he says, no, I'll stay, you let him stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.34,0:28:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A severely wounded warrior does not say, I think I'll stay, except once in a great while.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.75,0:28:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.24,0:28:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.66,0:28:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.90,0:28:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Accept karmic propensities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.20,0:28:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,See essence rather than perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.59,0:28:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the inner core?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.57,0:28:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner core of reality that this thing represents.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.74,0:29:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't reject the diamond just because it's a diamond, because the diamond could well be, you know, a keepsake left to you by your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.18,0:29:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the value of that diamond is not the monetary value of the diamond, but the fact that it was your mother's and she wore it during her whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.67,0:29:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want to see the essence of the thing rather than the story that you project onto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.20,0:29:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And jocular.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.79,0:29:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of morose, to be humorous and see the funny side of everything is uplifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.11,0:29:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's hard to be serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.73,0:29:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of very serious things, I have to watch myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.44,0:29:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to watch yourself because you've taken a more lighthearted view instead of being heavy-hearted.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.25,0:29:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any more?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.03,0:29:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,On this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.03,0:30:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This light, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.03,0:30:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there more?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.03,0:30:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Good will regarding all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.07,0:30:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the most important one of all, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.25,0:30:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To be of good will towards all of life and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.56,0:30:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Of good will towards the woods as you walk through the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.49,0:30:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the little bugs that you try to step around so you don't squish them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.97,0:30:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Of good will towards everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.49,0:30:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Good will regarding all of life and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.86,0:30:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To look at yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.97,0:30:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So love life as life, as an expression of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.73,0:30:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So one can see life is the radiance of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.04,0:30:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a good thing to love and guard and cherish.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.02,0:30:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To be easygoing rather than rigid.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.73,0:30:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't work this way, you let it go that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.93,0:30:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And then a person will say, but the ego says,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.23,0:30:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't that being wishy-washy?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.21,0:30:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Wishy-washy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.13,0:31:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd rather be wishy-washy and enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.23,0:31:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,than tough-minded and going to hell eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.64,0:31:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Reduce expectations of yourself and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.05,0:31:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If you find a seat on the subway, so much the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.05,0:31:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I like that story of the woman in the subway,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.46,0:31:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and she says to this gentleman sitting in the seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.00,0:31:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,she said, would you mind giving your seat to a pregnant woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.53,0:31:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Expectant mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.33,0:31:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.81,0:31:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And he looked at her, she looks sort of slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.68,0:31:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, how long have you been pregnant?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.90,0:31:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, oh, about an hour and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.96,0:31:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Be gracious to yourself and to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.39,0:31:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender the need to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.49,0:31:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the biggest one I think that people have.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.95,0:31:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to control everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.51,0:32:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanting to control others, other countries, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.46,0:32:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates about 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.81,0:32:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So certain organizations, some of them are religious, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.69,0:32:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,some political, some combine the two,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.68,0:32:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,want to conquer other countries just to control them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.07,0:32:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to control others just for the sake of control
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.77,0:32:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.53,0:32:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They can try to convince themselves that they're saving your soul,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.40,0:32:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but the reality is they just want to control you,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.98,0:32:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've got to see things their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.68,0:32:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.90,0:32:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.04,0:32:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.95,0:32:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Desire for applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.66,0:32:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's going to applaud when you're out in the woods
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.29,0:32:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and you save the life of some little animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.22,0:32:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't any applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.51,0:32:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the little rabbit, you take it home, you nurse it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.92,0:32:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,bring it back to health, it becomes a pet rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.04,0:32:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So the thing is self-rewarding.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.95,0:32:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to look for extraneous rewards.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.91,0:33:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The reward is in the gratification of the desire to be of assistance
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.36,0:33:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to that which is living.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.84,0:33:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I like, be glad instead of mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.39,0:33:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Be glad instead of mad that this incident has allowed you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.78,0:33:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize something about yourself and about life
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.45,0:33:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that you didn't know before.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.78,0:33:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.91,0:33:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad that I realize that now about myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.45,0:33:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad I realize that I'm selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.75,0:33:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.33,0:33:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize I was selfish before.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.52,0:33:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't want to put that much money in the plate at church.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.32,0:33:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.90,0:33:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You put a fiver in the plate and then you take three singles back out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.10,0:33:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Acceptance instead of resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.05,0:33:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Generous instead of stingy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.09,0:33:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Candid with yourself, honest, openly honest with yourself and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.81,0:34:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to learn how eventually to silence the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.77,0:34:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and give up thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.45,0:34:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very difficult to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.59,0:34:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you silence the mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.63,0:34:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you silence the mind and give up thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.25,0:34:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you do that by looking at the space around a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.38,0:34:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the thing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.73,0:34:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So I get this table as a generality in a greater generality.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.11,0:34:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I have any thoughts about this table?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.61,0:34:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.73,0:34:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any thoughts about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.71,0:34:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.46,0:34:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can look at a thing and let everything just be as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.01,0:34:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Without dissertation in your head about what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.88,0:34:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and what you should do about it and should you move it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.01,0:34:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and shouldn't that be a different color tablecloth, etc., etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.59,0:34:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can learn how to accept life on its own terms just as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.55,0:35:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the point of doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.21,0:35:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because then you live in a free state all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.73,0:35:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going, if it rains, it rains.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.48,0:35:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it doesn't rain, it doesn't rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.76,0:35:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's all the same one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.30,0:35:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If it rains, you get to accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.67,0:35:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to experience a rainy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.55,0:35:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it doesn't rain, you get to experience a sunny day.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.94,0:35:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't lose if you accept all possible alternatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.71,0:35:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If you die poor, you get put in a cheap grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.15,0:35:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you die rich, you get in a fancy cemetery.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.30,0:35:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A fancy cemetery is better, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.59,0:35:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Acceptance instead of resisting.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.13,0:35:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Being generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.61,0:35:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Honest with yourself instead of stingy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.53,0:35:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Honest with yourself and with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.61,0:35:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn how to silence the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.55,0:36:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up thinkingness means to look beyond it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.92,0:36:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Look beyond it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.65,0:36:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,To be forgiving instead of vindictive.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.82,0:36:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.13,0:36:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.32,0:36:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Work on your inner traits instead of the external ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.36,0:36:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.36,0:36:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether your shoes are shined is sort of interesting, but not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.11,0:36:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your inner traits.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.17,0:36:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your inner traits rather than your external ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.88,0:36:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It only takes a bone to make a dog happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.11,0:36:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.71,0:36:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It only takes a bone to make a dog happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.94,0:36:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My dog is happy all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.23,0:36:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear munch, munch, munch all night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.26,0:36:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It only takes a dog, I mean, a bone to make a dog happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.44,0:36:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And it only takes hiding the bone from the dog to make your wife happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.01,0:36:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.11,0:36:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.26,0:36:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.32,0:36:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.36,0:36:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.38,0:36:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.42,0:36:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.48,0:36:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.50,0:36:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.55,0:36:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.59,0:36:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.61,0:36:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.63,0:36:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.65,0:36:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.69,0:36:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.76,0:36:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.80,0:36:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.86,0:36:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.90,0:36:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.92,0:36:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.96,0:36:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.05,0:36:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.15,0:36:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.19,0:36:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.26,0:36:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.30,0:36:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.36,0:36:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.40,0:36:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.44,0:36:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.46,0:36:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.53,0:36:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.55,0:36:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.59,0:36:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.94,0:36:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That dog's going to chew on that bone all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.01,0:37:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, all right, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.86,0:37:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hear the dog gnawing away on the bone.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.96,0:37:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,After a while, I guess it does get irritating.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.90,0:37:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're trying to do it asleep, and the dog's going crunchy, crunchy, crunchy, crunchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.25,0:37:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What we really mean by all this is the small things of life are fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.07,0:37:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Small things of life are fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.57,0:37:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see very well, and so when I can't find my cane, somebody says, here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.44,0:37:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's your cane.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.86,0:37:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.90,0:37:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, oh, God, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.73,0:37:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.53,0:37:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where the thing was, and the small things of life make all the difference in the world, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.69,0:37:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a song that used to be, don't worry, be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.51,0:37:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember that song?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.63,0:37:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.26,0:37:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody remember that song?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.01,0:37:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.19,0:37:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.15,0:37:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Make that your song, and you can play that in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.28,0:37:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,While you're having breakfast, play, don't worry, be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.98,0:38:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And you go to work humming as you drive along in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.36,0:38:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Choose spiritual values and goals instead of material ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.90,0:38:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Like your ambition should be to be more forgiving, to be more loving, to be more generous,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.34,0:38:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to be of greater assistance to your fellow man,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.90,0:38:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things to make other living beings happy, whether it's animal, human, vegetable.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.34,0:38:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.09,0:38:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Choose spiritual friends and groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.00,0:38:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Go from complete to complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.80,0:38:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.63,0:38:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Choosing spiritual friends and groups makes a difference because you tend to become that with which you align.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.11,0:38:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you align with a strong spiritual group, you tend to become more and more that way yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.36,0:38:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you align with a sort of intemperate, hostile, violent, or hyper-religious group,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.53,0:38:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you tend to become like them, sort of spiteful and angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.36,0:38:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.23,0:39:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They actually have.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.26,0:39:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They have hate brigades.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.21,0:39:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.23,0:39:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I see it on television.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.26,0:39:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And some poor guy who's been shot overseas is being put in the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.03,0:39:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a hate group with hate signs.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.38,0:39:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how you get to heaven with a hate sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.84,0:39:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to leave your hate sign here to get to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.11,0:39:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.26,0:39:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They have hate groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.63,0:39:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.34,0:39:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Identify with the greater self rather than the small self.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.42,0:39:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Accept the limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.84,0:39:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The limitations of humanness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.92,0:39:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.32,0:39:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say, how can so much negativity and hostility?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.53,0:39:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the evolution of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.32,0:39:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind has not evolved to the angelic viewpoint, to the angelic point of being an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.55,0:39:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A human can become more and more angelic.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.15,0:40:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And eventually, if you become sufficiently angelic, you don't need to come back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.75,0:40:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you can if you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.28,0:40:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.38,0:40:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I have met angels in bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.57,0:40:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I have had angels stop and help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.11,0:40:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking now about the guy who circled around, circled around, came and got me out of the figure eight highway and went and got it changed and brought back.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.94,0:40:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That man was a saint.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.51,0:40:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.40,0:40:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.98,0:40:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.34,0:40:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are angels in bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.25,0:40:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something people don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.76,0:40:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This man.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.86,0:40:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on a cloverleaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.98,0:40:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In my old truck, and it broke down.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.84,0:40:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There I am stuck on a cloverleaf with a broken down truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.90,0:40:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, in the middle of nowhere, and this car pulled over and the guy says, you in trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.03,0:40:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, yeah, he won't start.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.38,0:40:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, here, let me help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.11,0:40:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Complete stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.32,0:41:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He got out the lug lug wrench and took the lugs off the tire through the tire and all in the back of his pickup truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.00,0:41:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He drove, drove half a mile away, went around the cloverleaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.92,0:41:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Took it, took the truck tire to a repair station, had it repaired, came back to cloverleaf, came back to cloverleaf, came back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.44,0:41:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It all took about an hour and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.03,0:41:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, he had to put out the money to get the tire fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.09,0:41:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, I gave him the money and I thanked him profusely, but that's the first one I ever did.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.65,0:41:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The ironman.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.13,0:41:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, that man, he was an angel angel in a human body.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.53,0:41:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are, there are actual angels.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.30,0:41:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Within a human body, uh, we can evolve to that ourself by our own inner decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.46,0:41:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.80,0:41:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.13,0:41:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.25,0:41:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to croak, get run over.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.44,0:42:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become angelic while you're still in a physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.90,0:42:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.75,0:42:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We will become the first angelic group in the history of mankind, a group of angels, 900 angels.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.30,0:42:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All at one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.15,0:42:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, some people in this group are already angelic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.55,0:42:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.07,0:42:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They already got that ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.13,0:42:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We already have angels sitting in the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.59,0:42:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We're $5.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.28,0:42:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I introduce you to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.01,0:42:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not $5.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.00,0:42:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A generous donation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.78,0:42:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.05,0:42:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.23,0:42:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.38,0:42:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But, uh, that's a discovery we made.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.76,0:42:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's pretty original with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.53,0:42:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Our.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.76,0:43:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Our work that, um, there are literally angels incarnate, actually angels here living amongst
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.86,0:43:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,us and reading it, radiating out goodness, uh, to mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.03,0:43:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are very fortunate then in this group, there are angels that have returned to a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.32,0:43:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.11,0:43:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.84,0:43:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that life is a learning curve, so you never have to be dissatisfied with.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.09,0:43:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yourself because you're doing as well as you can at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.40,0:43:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could be doing better, you would be so being self critical, then it's always arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.57,0:43:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could be better, you would be the fact that you're not means you can't right now because you haven't reached that goal yet to be forgiving towards people who cut in on you on traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.03,0:43:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, this is you're pulling up a car pulls right in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.94,0:44:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to be angelic, not the curse, the guy, you know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.90,0:44:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of you bless a person who pulls in front of you in traffic?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.86,0:44:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Any hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.09,0:44:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is a truthful group.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.01,0:44:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A truthful group.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.67,0:44:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, it's hard to bless the person who pulls in in front of you, but let's try that as a group experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.05,0:44:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Henceforth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.61,0:44:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody is rude to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.94,0:44:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In traffic and pulls in in front of you, forgive them for being somewhat impaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.80,0:44:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they they they lack being gracious and thoughtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.69,0:44:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, maybe they got to go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.28,0:44:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.67,0:44:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they're intoxicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.65,0:44:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But we could practice in traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.40,0:45:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See, it's one thing to be spiritual on Sunday morning in church with all the hymns and the music and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.21,0:45:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's another to be spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.13,0:45:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.82,0:45:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're in the middle of traffic, so that would be a good exercise we could do as a group, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.59,0:45:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was a cab driver for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.53,0:45:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I drove a cab.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.38,0:45:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I drove a truck and, uh, all right, we could do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.71,0:45:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because, you know, being holy, being a holy rolly in church is easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.86,0:45:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The hymns and the music and the Oregon and everybody's also goody pod, goody, goody, goody pie next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.01,0:45:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.13,0:45:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So that could be a practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.38,0:45:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We could become our practice that we recommend new people want to come in the group with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.98,0:45:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, listen to what the rules are.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.23,0:46:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be loving and gracious and forgiving towards everybody in traffic, no matter what they do, even if they pull pull up in front of you and slam the brake on, you still have to be forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.96,0:46:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good discipline, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.86,0:46:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can be forgiving in church and pious and holy and all that rolly.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.84,0:46:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.96,0:46:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.26,0:46:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul, you've been this happiness is a destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.69,0:46:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.07,0:46:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a endpoint or no beginning and no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.44,0:46:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Being happy is a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.17,0:46:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being in this world to make the best of every situation to the best that you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.26,0:46:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual lifestyle is reflective versus impulsive.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.84,0:46:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It tends to be reflective.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.05,0:46:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees how you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.15,0:47:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're rude to that person in traffic to get even with them, so it's reflective, and it says that was pretty rude on my part, and at the time you did it, you justified it, but now when you reflect on it, you say that really wasn't a very gracious or a wonderful thing I did there, and so you decide to do better, so you're constantly learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.46,0:47:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A truly spiritual person is constantly learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.53,0:47:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We're learning, and get something out of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.82,0:47:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's reflective versus impulsive.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.05,0:47:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's thoughtful rather than critical, and it tends to be content instead of complaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.73,0:47:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of complaining about circumstances, what we do is we commit to a style of life that will bring us closer and closer to our goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.50,0:47:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.13,0:47:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To be more and more self-forgiving instead of self-critical, and you say, yeah, I was selfish right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.92,0:48:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I did take the last donut.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.69,0:48:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I did take the last donut.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.09,0:48:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Went out for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.98,0:48:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not take the last donut.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.38,0:48:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gooder than them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.53,0:48:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.09,0:48:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So we get a sense of what's.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.17,0:48:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.51,0:48:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of holding values of yourself and the human condition so that you're forgiving at all times, no matter how life goes, that you did the best you could.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.00,0:48:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can always attack yourself with the hypotheticals and say, well, I could have done better.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.73,0:48:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could have, you would have.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.90,0:48:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you don't do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.59,0:48:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you really can't in a certain state of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.46,0:49:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only when you're in a different state of mind that you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.80,0:49:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So self-criticism, self-awareness is different than self-criticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.09,0:49:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,To be self-aware, you realize you could have been more generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.00,0:49:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-criticism is attacking yourself for not being more generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.50,0:49:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.96,0:49:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to be spiritual than self-critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.98,0:49:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is a learning curve.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.32,0:49:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.23,0:49:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And do we have any more slides?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.40,0:49:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.07,0:49:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When in doubt, pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.42,0:49:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.15,0:49:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.01,0:49:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When I think of the times in my life that I really prayed, other than going to church and some great cathedral, you know, that's a certain style of praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.67,0:49:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But when a certain death is looking you right in the eye, that's when you really pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.01,0:49:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.15,0:50:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're about to.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.42,0:50:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.88,0:50:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's this mind floating next to the ship, and it's about to explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.96,0:50:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says, he was scared to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.75,0:50:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said to him, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.46,0:50:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, it's not going to go off.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.71,0:50:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And besides, even if it does, the only thing that can happen is she'll die.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.28,0:50:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.55,0:50:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And instantly his fear left him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.46,0:50:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly his fear left him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.61,0:50:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a huge mind that was starting to bump against the side of the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.13,0:50:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're trying to hold it away with this gaffing, gaff hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.51,0:50:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says, what if it explodes?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.13,0:50:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, I said, well, then we die.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.15,0:50:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.51,0:50:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,End of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.23,0:50:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,End of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.30,0:50:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When you accept the worst possible scenario, accept the worst possible scenario, that's another way of getting rid of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.11,0:50:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Someday you're going to be old and ugly and blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.23,0:50:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, well, I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.55,0:51:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm at least that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.92,0:51:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There, one eyed blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.82,0:51:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I ain't so good looking as I once was.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.05,0:51:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.28,0:51:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we seek through prayer and contemplation.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.23,0:51:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Affirm that God is my source and my solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.73,0:51:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sing an inner voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.82,0:51:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's something you don't read about.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.98,0:51:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But you pick an inner song that pleases you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.73,0:51:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I like what the...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.73,0:51:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What the bagpiper played today.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.44,0:51:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, I could play his song, that song within my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.63,0:51:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.82,0:51:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.59,0:51:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.90,0:51:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that's my song.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.57,0:51:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And especially on bagpipes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.94,0:51:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing Grace is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.63,0:52:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have great hopes that at my funeral, the bagpiper will be playing Amazing Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.53,0:52:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If not, you'll hear about it later when you come over.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.42,0:52:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, where was the bagpiper, for God's sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.17,0:52:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sing an inner song.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.34,0:52:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Amazing Grace makes a beautiful song.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.40,0:52:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That type of an uplifting, purely spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.11,0:52:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing Grace itself is, you know, strictly spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.21,0:52:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not religious, spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.84,0:52:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.03,0:52:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When feeling down, say to yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.01,0:52:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is the saddest story I've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.38,0:53:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Every once in a while, I give you little clues about things to write and put on your mirror at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.32,0:53:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that you can post in the corner of your mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.69,0:53:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.17,0:53:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is the saddest story I have ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.19,0:53:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I've recommended that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.01,0:53:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people have yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.13,0:53:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is the saddest story I've ever heard on their mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.42,0:53:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.28,0:53:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A few?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.51,0:53:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.05,0:53:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Best thing to do is write it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.32,0:53:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is the saddest story I've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.78,0:53:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Underline is.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.67,0:53:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We already said it's the saddest story.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.36,0:53:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But we should underline is.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.90,0:53:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So after this lecture, I want you to underline is.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.61,0:53:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is the saddest story I've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.28,0:53:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,After the lecture, I want you to underline is.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.92,0:54:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The next lecture, we'll underline saddest.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.05,0:54:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the saddest.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.26,0:54:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The is good, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.76,0:54:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the saddest story I have ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.19,0:54:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to underline ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.07,0:54:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.75,0:54:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're poor, dumb, and ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.92,0:54:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.86,0:54:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody hates you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.69,0:54:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were a kid, we sang a song.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.55,0:54:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody hates you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.84,0:54:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody hates me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.46,0:54:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess I'll go eat worms.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.28,0:54:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody hates me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.53,0:54:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess I'll go eat worms.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.98,0:54:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess I'll go eat worms.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.84,0:54:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's another handy sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.21,0:54:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could change signs during the month.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.00,0:54:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't get bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.01,0:54:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is the saddest story.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.59,0:55:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll go and eat worms.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.71,0:55:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I like, even God feels sorry for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.28,0:55:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember that song, that story about Wallaby.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.55,0:55:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything goes wrong with his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.65,0:55:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he's poor and crippled.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.92,0:55:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,His girlfriend leaves him.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.36,0:55:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, God?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.80,0:55:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The voice comes out of the heaven and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.09,0:55:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, Wallaby, there's just something
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.84,0:55:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,about you pissing me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.69,0:55:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I always liked that story.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.13,0:55:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.05,0:55:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Play the role of martyr and justice collector.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.86,0:55:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Play the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.98,0:55:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is a cessation, pray and contemplate.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.07,0:56:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Insist on, why me, God?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.44,0:56:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do my slides slide all over?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.73,0:56:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it doesn't bother me because I am courageous
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.46,0:56:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will succeed no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.53,0:56:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, when you're down and out,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.63,0:56:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what's wrong is you fight it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.55,0:56:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're down and out and you're fighting
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.82,0:56:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,being miserable and gloomy,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.59,0:56:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,insist on being miserable and gloomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.36,0:57:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Your socks don't match.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.78,0:57:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a hole in one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.61,0:57:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All your shirts are dirty and wrinkled.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.82,0:57:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The bed clothing fell on the floor during the night
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.51,0:57:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cat slept on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.23,0:57:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all very handy things.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.01,0:57:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.25,0:57:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Make faces at yourself in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.59,0:57:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.07,0:57:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody done that?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.28,0:57:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.90,0:57:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great one.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.40,0:57:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that one you can't make faces at yourself in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.07,0:57:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you look at the ceiling and you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.80,0:58:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's hard to stay depressed and visible
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.11,0:58:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when you make faces at yourself in the mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.46,0:58:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because the whole thing is,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.78,0:58:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a hard time seeing myself in the mirror now.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.75,0:58:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have a hard time making faces at myself in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.09,0:58:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I go like this and I got lights on myself trying,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.57,0:58:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to find some other way to torment myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.42,0:58:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Be grateful for the gift of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.03,0:58:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When everything else settles down and you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.42,0:58:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,well, this is wrong, this is wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.76,0:58:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,these things have happened to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.57,0:58:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but I've had the gift of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.17,0:58:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And by living the gift of life in a certain way,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.40,0:58:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I have great hopes and looking forward to the afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.67,0:58:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So we live one day at a time and do the best we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.26,0:58:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to be your own best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.26,0:59:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.05,0:59:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to choose whether you're gonna expand
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.25,0:59:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,on a problem or diminish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.30,0:59:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you gonna be a diminisher or an expander?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.38,0:59:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my God, we're out of eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.36,0:59:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Or we're out of eggs so we'll have cereal.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.55,0:59:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, which way you can have it either one way,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.65,0:59:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,your day is either ruined, we're all out of eggs,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.55,0:59:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or you can be happy, oh great,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.51,0:59:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll be out of cereal for a change.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.67,0:59:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarify the confusion of your capital S self,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.78,0:59:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with your social role.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.05,0:59:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The self is one thing, your social role is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.28,0:59:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you can be in the higher self
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.38,0:59:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and fulfill any social role without changing identification.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.92,0:59:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Play the role of martyr or the injustice collector.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.01,0:59:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Play the role of the hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.61,0:59:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the option to play the role of the victim
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.71,1:00:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or the hero, play the role of morally, socially,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.96,1:00:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,superior. Gooder than
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.90,1:00:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you. Yep. Let go
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.13,1:00:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of being an injustice collector.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.01,1:00:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, how unjust it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.65,1:00:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we watch that all day on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.11,1:00:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a competition
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.40,1:00:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for injustice collectors.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.82,1:00:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's the most
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.71,1:00:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,martyred? Let go of being
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.42,1:00:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,provocative to others.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.82,1:00:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time you see yourself getting provocative,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.67,1:00:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, well, I
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.59,1:00:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,may be triggered that. So see
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.46,1:00:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself as the trigger of events.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.34,1:00:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you see
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.05,1:00:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,an event happen in your life that you're not
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.38,1:00:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,happy about, ask,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.36,1:00:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,how could I
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.98,1:00:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,have been the trigger of that instead of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.30,1:00:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,blaming it on the other person?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.53,1:00:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The other person's impatient.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.71,1:00:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get mad at them for
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.40,1:00:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,being impatient. Then you realize you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.21,1:00:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,kept them waiting for 10 minutes while you stood
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.40,1:00:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,there and brushed your teeth.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.19,1:00:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop pushing your luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.86,1:01:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.78,1:01:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not buy a house
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.90,1:01:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the floodplain
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.84,1:01:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or on the edge of a mine
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.44,1:01:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,mud cliff.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.05,1:01:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day there's a sad
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.59,1:01:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,story. Went out
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.61,1:01:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,all by himself in the jungle
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.75,1:01:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and got lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.92,1:01:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Built a house on the edge of the mud cliff
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.94,1:01:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mud cliff slid down
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.44,1:01:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,along with your house.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.15,1:01:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask yourself, who in the world would build
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.26,1:01:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,a house on the edge of a mud cliff?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.65,1:01:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They do it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.65,1:01:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can drive down certain places
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.11,1:01:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the California coast, sure enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.46,1:01:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Mud cliff? House.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.03,1:01:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The house is just edging itself
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.15,1:01:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,closer and closer to the edge.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.15,1:01:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say to Susan, I don't know how people
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.78,1:01:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,can live
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.21,1:01:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that close to a cliff
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.23,1:01:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in the mud cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.92,1:01:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Let go of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.19,1:01:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,being a justice collector. Let go of being
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.98,1:02:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,provocative. Stop pushing
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.03,1:02:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,one's luck. Avoid
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.09,1:02:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophe. People like to say
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.03,1:02:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.44,1:02:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,responsible for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.94,1:02:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Last week I had a doctor's appointment at 9 in the morning
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.40,1:02:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the weather,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.01,1:02:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the weather news said there was going to be
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.36,1:02:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a, what do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.92,1:02:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Tornado, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.78,1:02:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather news said tornado. Stay off
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.84,1:02:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Route 89A.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.46,1:02:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of pushing our luck and then blaming it
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.78,1:02:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,on the weather, we just
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.65,1:02:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,canceled the doctor's appointment.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.59,1:02:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Simple enough, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.26,1:02:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can see how many people would push it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.88,1:02:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,keep the doctor's appointment,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.75,1:02:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,go off the road, be taken away by
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.63,1:02:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a tow truck and have a long
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.75,1:02:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,sad story.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.25,1:02:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.25,1:02:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,keep pushing your luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.73,1:02:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.73,1:02:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not buy a house in the flood plain
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.73,1:02:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or the edge of a mud cliff.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.73,1:02:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not win the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.05,1:02:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever see the story of what happens in people's lives
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.05,1:02:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,who win the lottery?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.05,1:03:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The divorce rate is close to 100%.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.05,1:03:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Murder, suicide, divorce, and surprisingly, half of them
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.05,1:03:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,become bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.05,1:03:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you win the lottery and go bankrupt?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.05,1:03:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They figured out how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.05,1:03:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not ski in an avalanche area.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.05,1:03:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have a car.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.05,1:03:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have a car.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.21,1:03:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have a car. Don't have a car.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.38,1:03:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have a car. Don't have a car.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.51,1:03:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have a car. Don't have a car.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.51,1:03:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have a car.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.51,1:03:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,ents expand your value plan over 10%
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.61,1:03:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,price, watercolor,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.59,1:03:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,great big climbers, I would make them post a
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.59,1:03:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a bond with the state.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.84,1:03:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to post a $10,000 bound if you're going to climb Mount Everest.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.67,1:03:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The 90 people who didn't make it have cost the taxpayers a fortune.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.88,1:03:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're going to climb Mount Everest,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.51,1:04:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to post a $10 million bond with the Parks Department.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.03,1:04:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Obey the law, be polite to the police.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.42,1:04:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things seem so simple,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.28,1:04:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet every day on the news I see people mouth off to the police.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.75,1:04:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A cop is the last person I think I would mouth off to.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.48,1:04:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So stop demonstrating.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.17,1:04:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, there's another one that gets me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.38,1:04:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day you see demonstrators out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.01,1:04:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got these big signs because they're going to demonstrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.11,1:04:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always think, who cares what you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.19,1:04:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They're pro this or they're against that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.86,1:04:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would anybody care what you think about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.07,1:04:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, they take it very seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.86,1:04:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop demonstrating.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.59,1:04:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good idea to give up saving the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.38,1:04:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a really good idea to mind your own business.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.03,1:05:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego doesn't want to hear mind your own business.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.51,1:05:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my responsibility as a citizen to get out there and demonstrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.03,1:05:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My responsibility to get out there and demonstrate as a citizen.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.94,1:05:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.30,1:05:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up being important.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.69,1:05:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's it, demonstrators.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.98,1:05:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, what goes on with demonstrators?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.26,1:05:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you get a feeling of being important.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.26,1:05:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, another idea is pay your income taxes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.34,1:05:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This never seems to dawn on the leaders of our country.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.34,1:05:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They're in the big-name leader out there who isn't behind on their income taxes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.13,1:05:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever notice that?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.59,1:05:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the funniest thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.59,1:05:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter who they are, the president's cabinet is made up of people who do not pay their income taxes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.03,1:05:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.92,1:06:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the head of the tax department hasn't paid his taxes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.76,1:06:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.00,1:06:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Lastly, smile and the world smiles with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.94,1:06:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Cry and you cry alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.63,1:06:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dedicate all your actions to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.53,1:06:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what happens if you dedicate all your actions to God is they automatically become changed and purified.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.84,1:06:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If you dedicate this demonstration to God,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.55,1:06:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to fool yourself into thinking that your ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.03,1:06:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.03,1:06:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because nobody's going to be pleased about your demonstration except you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.61,1:06:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of these steps that we talk about bring about an inner humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.28,1:06:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the inner humility,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.57,1:06:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you stop listening to the voice of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.82,1:06:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and in its place reigns the silence of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.34,1:06:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and that God is all that is becomes readily apparent without a single thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.40,1:06:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.88,1:07:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The divinity of all that exists shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.00,1:07:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All that exists is divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.17,1:07:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else except divinity exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.38,1:07:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Without divinity, there's no sky, there's no earth, there's no table,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.63,1:07:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no Susie, there's no audience.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.57,1:07:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that exists is divinity, period.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.34,1:07:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else exists except divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.86,1:07:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,God in the infinite number of expressions,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.90,1:07:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,as people, as stage, as sarni,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.19,1:07:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as tea, as cane, as a cup of coffee.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.17,1:07:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to exist is solely that of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.71,1:07:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just said is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.82,1:07:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Zowie.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.78,1:07:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That ought to do it for today.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.42,1:08:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that is, everything that exists is an expression of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.03,1:08:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity as this cane, as this table, as this Kleenex.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.30,1:08:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only two things.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.40,1:08:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,One is existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.10,1:08:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.85,1:08:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.32,1:08:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All that exists is divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.10,1:08:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes life simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.10,1:08:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.85,1:08:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.35,1:08:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, honey.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.27,1:08:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see.
